            <title>[KAFKA-13374] [Docs] - All reads from the leader of the partition even after KIP-392?</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-13374</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;On `&lt;a href=&quot;https://kafka.apache.org/documentation/#design_replicatedlog&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://kafka.apache.org/documentation/#design_replicatedlog&lt;/a&gt;` it says&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt; All reads and writes go to the leader of the partition.&lt;/p&gt;



&lt;p&gt;However with KIP-392 I didn&apos;t think this was the case any more. If so, the doc should be updated to clarify.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
